# Régimes politiques libéraux

~? Régime politique :
^une manière // {"headword":"manière","category":"noun","gender":"feminine","cefrLevel":"A2"}
^un pouvoir // {"headword":"pouvoir","category":"noun","gender":"masculine","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^un état // {"headword":"état","category":"noun","gender":"masculine","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^organiser // {"headword":"organiser","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"A2"}
^exercer // {"headword":"exercer","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B2"}
**manière dont** le **pouvoir** est **organisé** et **exercé** dans un état.

^un type // {"headword":"type","category":"noun","gender":"masculine","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^politique // {"headword":"politique","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"A2"}
~? **Types** de **régimes politiques** **libéraux** :
- présidentiel
- parlementaire
- semi-présidentiel

~? Régime **présidentiel** :
^un pouvoir exécutif // {"headword":"pouvoir exécutif","category":"noun","gender":"masculine","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^concentrer // {"headword":"concentrer","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^élu // {"headword":"élu","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B1"}
- pouvoir **exécutif** **concentré entre** les **mains** d'un **président élu**
^États-Unis // {"headword":"États-Unis","category":"noun"}
^Brésil // {"headword":"Brésil","category":"noun"}
- exemples : **États-Unis**, **Brésil**

^un parlement // {"headword":"parlement","category":"noun","gender":"masculine","cefrLevel":"B2"}
~? Régime **parlementaire** :
^un gouvernement // {"headword":"gouvernement","category":"noun","gender":"masculine","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^renverser quelque chose // {"headword":"renverser quelque chose","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^responsable // {"headword":"responsable","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"A2"}
- **gouvernement** **responsable devant** le **parlement** qui **peut** le **renverser**
^un chef d'État // {"headword":"chef d'État","category":"noun","gender":"masculine","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^représentatif // {"headword":"représentatif","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^symbolique // {"headword":"symbolique","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B2"}
- **chef d'État** **représentatif** ou **symbolique**
^Royaume-Uni // {"headword":"Royaume-Uni","category":"noun"}
^Allemagne // {"headword":"Allemagne","category":"noun"}
- exemples : **Royaume-Uni**, **Allemagne**

^semi // {"headword":"semi","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B2"}
~? Régime semi-présidentiel :
- président élu
^devant // {"headword":"devant","category":"other","cefrLevel":"A1"}
- **gouvernement** **responsable** **devant** le **parlement**
- exemple : **France**

# Liberal Political Systems

~? Political system:
^the way // {"headword":"way","category":"noun","cefrLevel":"A1"}
^the power // {"headword":"power","category":"noun","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^the state // {"headword":"state","category":"noun","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^organize // {"headword":"organize","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^exercise // {"headword":"exercise","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B2"}
**way in which** **power** is **organized** and **exercised** in a state.

^the type // {"headword":"type","category":"noun","cefrLevel":"A2"}
^political // {"headword":"political","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B1"}
~? Types of liberal political systems:
- presidential
- parliamentary
- semi-presidential

~? Presidential system:
^the executive power // {"headword":"executive power","category":"noun","cefrLevel":"C1"}
^concentrate // {"headword":"concentrate","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^elected // {"headword":"elected","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B1"}
- **executive power** **concentrated in** the **hands** of an **elected president**
^United States // {"headword":"United States","category":"noun"}
^Brazil // {"headword":"Brazil","category":"noun"}
- examples: **United States**, **Brazil**

^the parliament // {"headword":"parliament","category":"noun","cefrLevel":"B2"}
~? Parliamentary system:
^the government // {"headword":"government","category":"noun","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^dismiss something // {"headword":"dismiss something","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^accountable // {"headword":"accountable","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"C1"}
- **government** **accountable to** the **parliament** which **can** **dismiss** it
^the head of state // {"headword":"head of state","category":"noun","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^representative // {"headword":"representative","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^symbolic // {"headword":"symbolic","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B2"}
- **head of state** is **representative** or **symbolic**
^United Kingdom // {"headword":"United Kingdom","category":"noun"}
^Germany // {"headword":"Germany","category":"noun"}
- examples: **United Kingdom**, **Germany**

^semi // {"headword":"semi","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B2"}
~? Semi-presidential system:
- elected president
^to // {"headword":"to","category":"other","cefrLevel":"A1"}
- **government** **accountable** **to** the **parliament**
- example: **France**

# Liberale politische Systeme

~? Politisches System:
^die Art und Weise // {"headword":"Art und Weise","category":"noun","gender":"feminine","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^die Macht // {"headword":"Macht","category":"noun","gender":"feminine","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^der Staat // {"headword":"Staat","category":"noun","gender":"masculine","cefrLevel":"A2"}
^organisieren // {"headword":"organisieren","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^ausüben // {"headword":"ausüben","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B2"}
**Art und Weise, wie** die **Macht** im **Staat organisiert** und **ausgeübt** wird.

^die Art // {"headword":"Art","category":"noun","gender":"feminine","cefrLevel":"A2"}
^politisch // {"headword":"politisch","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B1"}
~?Arten liberaler politischer Systeme:
- präsidentiell
- parlamentarisch
- semi-präsidentiell

~? Präsidentielles System:
^die Exekutivgewalt // {"headword":"Exekutivgewalt","category":"noun","gender":"feminine","cefrLevel":"C1"}
^konzentrieren // {"headword":"konzentrieren","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^gewählt // {"headword":"gewählt","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B1"}
- **Exekutivgewalt** **konzentriert in** den **Händen** eines **gewählten Präsidenten**
^Vereinigte Staaten // {"headword":"Vereinigte Staaten","category":"noun"}
^Brasilien // {"headword":"Brasilien","category":"noun"}
- Beispiele: **Vereinigte Staaten**, **Brasilien**

^das Parlament // {"headword":"Parlament","category":"noun","gender":"neuter","cefrLevel":"B1"}
~? Parlamentarisches System:
^die Regierung // {"headword":"Regierung","category":"noun","gender":"feminine","cefrLevel":"B1"}
^etwas abwählen // {"headword":"etwas abwählen","category":"verb","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^verantwortlich // {"headword":"verantwortlich","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B1"}
- **Regierung** **verantwortlich gegenüber** dem **Parlament**, das sie **abwählen kann**
^das Staatsoberhaupt // {"headword":"Staatsoberhaupt","category":"noun","gender":"neuter","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^repräsentativ // {"headword":"repräsentativ","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B2"}
^symbolisch // {"headword":"symbolisch","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"B2"}
- **Staatsoberhaupt** **repräsentativ** oder **symbolisch**
^Vereinigtes Königreich // {"headword":"Vereinigtes Königreich","category":"noun"}
^Deutschland // {"headword":"Deutschland","category":"noun"}
- Beispiele: **Vereinigtes Königreich**, **Deutschland**

^semi // {"headword":"semi","category":"adjective","cefrLevel":"C1"}
~? Semi-präsidentielles System:
- gewählter Präsident
^gegenüber // {"headword":"gegenüber","category":"other","cefrLevel":"B1"}
- **Regierung** **verantwortlich** **gegenüber** dem **Parlament**
- Beispiel: **Frankreich**
